.docname {Digital Twin Service}
.include {docs}

Implementation reference for the `twin-service`. For its architectural role, see [Digital Twin Service Architecture](../architecture/twin-architecture.qd); for the domain model, see [Building Management](../domain/building-management.qd).

A Node.js / Express service in TypeScript. It is the spatial source of truth: it stores buildings and rooms, and on every change it synchronises a lightweight clone to the dependent services.

---

## Source Layout

.var {headers}
   - Path
   - Responsibility

.tablebyrows {.headers}
    - - `src/router.ts`
      - Route table for building CRUD, plus health, metrics, and the `/contracts` metric catalog.
    - - `src/controller/buildings.ts`
      - HTTP adapters over the building service.
    - - `src/services/buildings.ts`
      - Core CRUD logic and orchestration of downstream synchronisation.
    - - `src/services/names.ts`
      - Pure helpers for normalising and backfilling building/room display names.
    - - `src/services/sensors.ts`
      - Pushes the threshold clone to the sensor-service.
    - - `src/services/contractsService.ts`
      - Seeds default display preferences in the contracts-service.
    - - `src/models/building.ts`
      - Mongoose schema for `Building`, `Room`, and the geometry value objects.

---

